        <h2>How community posting works</h2>
        <p>WPCNA accepts submissions from residents and community organizations for information that is relevant to White Plains neighborhoods. All submissions are reviewed before anything is posted or shared.</p>

        <p>This is a curated, community-serving channel — not an open bulletin board. We share things that help residents stay informed about civic life, neighborhood activity, and public-interest events in White Plains.</p>

        <h3>What we share</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Community events (school picnics, neighborhood gatherings, block parties)</li>
          <li>Neighborhood initiatives (cleanups, safety walks, beautification efforts)</li>
          <li>Civic and educational programs</li>
          <li>City notices (hydrant flushing, road work, public hearings)</li>
          <li>Sustainability and awareness campaigns</li>
          <li>Local nonprofit and community organization announcements</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What we don't share</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Yard sales or personal listings</li>
          <li>Business advertising or promotions</li>
          <li>Commercial services or solicitations</li>
          <li>Unreviewed or anonymous submissions</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Everything posted through WPCNA should be <strong>community-serving</strong>, <strong>non-commercial</strong>, and <strong>relevant to White Plains residents</strong>.</p>

        <h2>How to submit</h2>
        <p>Use the Community Postings submission form with a clear subject line and the details you would like shared. Please include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>A brief description of what you are sharing</li>
          <li>Relevant dates, times, and locations</li>
          <li>A contact name and organization (if applicable)</li>
          <li>Any links or attachments</li>
        </ul>
        <p>WPCNA reviews all submissions. Not everything sent will be posted, and we may edit for clarity or length. If you have questions about whether something fits, just ask.</p>
      </article>

